The article discusses Mick Mulvaney's first day as the Director of the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) and his approach to advancing President Trump's goals. Mulvaney emphasizes the importance of ensuring the President can keep his promises and highlights the expertise of the career staff at OMB. The article also mentions the crafting of a budget that prioritizes American security and fiscal responsibility. This includes a $54 billion investment in the military, border security, veterans' healthcare, and school choice. The budget blueprint also aims to eliminate redundant or ineffective programs. Mulvaney is committed to working towards making America great again, in line with the President's vision.